%% Diagram: CvRDT vs CmRDT vs delta-state — what travels over the wire
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Replica A
    participant N as Network
    participant B as Replica B
    Note over A,B: State-based (CvRDT)<br/>any delivery order, dups OK
    A->>N: full state S_A (large)
    N->>B: full state S_A
    B->>B: S_B := S_A ⊔ S_B
    Note over A,B: Operation-based (CmRDT)<br/>requires causal exactly-once
    A->>N: op (small)
    N->>B: op (in causal order)
    B->>B: apply(op)
    Note over A,B: Delta-state<br/>any delivery order, peer sync vector
    A->>N: delta δ since v_B (small)
    N->>B: delta δ
    B->>B: S_B := S_B ⊔ δ
